## **ðŸŽ¯ Complete Functionality Implementation:**

### **âœ… Central Agent Watching End-to-End Shipments**
- `app/services/orchestrator.py` - Central orchestrator monitors all shipments
- Real-time monitoring loops
- Database integration for shipment tracking

### **âœ… Risk Detection (Port Congestion, Customs Delays, Quality Holds)**
- `app/services/risk_service.py` - Comprehensive risk detection
- `app/mcp/servers/risk_detector.py` - MCP agent for risk detection
- Specific detection methods for each risk type

### **âœ… Simulation of Mitigation Options**
- `app/services/simulation_service.py` - Digital twin simulation engine
- What-if analysis for different scenarios
- Cost-benefit analysis of mitigation options

### **âœ… Execution of Actions (Re-routing, Mode-Switching)**
- `app/services/action_service.py` - Action execution service
- Support for rerouting, mode switching, expedited customs, etc.
- Database updates and event publishing

### **âœ… Stakeholder Communication Coordination**
- `app/services/communication_service.py` - Multi-channel communication
- `app/mcp/servers/stakeholder_comms.py` - MCP agent for AI-powered communication
- Personalized messages for different stakeholders

### **âœ… Real-time Functionality**
- `app/api/websocket.py` - WebSocket endpoints for real-time updates
- Redis pub/sub for event distribution
- Live dashboard with streaming updates

### **âœ… MCP (Model Context Protocol) Integration**
- Complete MCP server implementations for all agents
- Agent-to-agent communication protocol
- Centralized agent coordination

### **âœ… Digital Tower Visualization**
- Streamlit frontend with real-time visualization
- Agent network visualization
- Live shipment tracking map
- Risk heatmaps and analytics

## **ðŸš€ Running the Complete System:**

```bash
# 1. Clone and setup
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your OpenAI API key

# 2. Start all services
make up

# 3. Initialize database and seed data
make migrate
make seed

# 4. Access applications
# Frontend Dashboard: http://localhost:8501
# API Documentation: http://localhost:8000/docs
# RabbitMQ Management: http://localhost:15672 (guest/guest)
# MCP Agents: Running in separate containers

# 5. Test the system
# Create a shipment via API
# Watch risk detection in action
# See autonomous actions being executed
# Monitor real-time updates in dashboard